        </div>
        <div class="sd-anatomy">
          <div class="piece">
            <div class="k">Part 01</div>
            <h4>The brief</h4>
            <p>One line that tells Claude when to step in. <em>"Use me whenever I'm writing an investment memo."</em></p>
          </div>
          <div class="piece">
            <div class="k">Part 02</div>
            <h4>The playbook</h4>
            <p>How you actually do the work. Your steps, your tone, examples of what <em>good</em> looks like — and what doesn't.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="piece">
            <div class="k">Part 03</div>
            <h4>The toolkit</h4>
            <p>Optional. Templates and shortcuts Claude can reach for — your deck template, your Excel formulas, your boilerplate.</p>
