    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 11 · Phase 1 — Stop one-shotting ═══ -->
    <section class="card-deck-card deck-slide slide-phase p1" data-slide="plan-phase-1">
      <div class="phase-content stagger">
        <div class="phase-head">
          <div class="phase-head-left">
            <span class="phase-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <div class="phase-label">Phase 01 · Weeks 1 → 4</div>
              <h1 class="phase-title">Stop <em>one-shotting</em>.</h1>
            </div>
          </div>
          <span class="phase-subhead">The Loop, into muscle memory →</span>
        </div>

        <div class="week-grid cols4">
          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 01</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Scan the field.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Run the <em>same task</em> through Claude, ChatGPT, and Gemini. Where does each one win?</li>
              <li>Tag every real task as <em>Know · Do · Show</em> before you start.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 02</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Prep before you prompt.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Ask AI to <em>interview you</em> before it starts the task.</li>
              <li>Ask AI to <em>rewrite your prompt</em> before you run it.</li>
              <li class="carry keep"><span class="ctag">Keep</span>cross-check 2+ models</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 03</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Direct, don't dictate.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Show <em>good and bad examples</em> from your past work.</li>
              <li><em>3–5 passes</em>, minimum. No first answers.</li>
              <li class="carry keep"><span class="ctag">Keep</span>AI interviews you first</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 04</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Don't ship raw.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Push back. Ask what AI <em>held back</em>. Ask what would make it better.</li>
              <li><em>Humanize.</em> Deslop every edge.</li>
              <li class="carry keep"><span class="ctag">Keep</span>examples · iteration · cross-check</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="slide-num">11 · Phase 1</div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 17 · Phase 2 — Sessions become your SOP ═══ -->
    <section class="card-deck-card deck-slide slide-phase p2" data-slide="plan-phase-2">
      <div class="phase-content stagger">
        <div class="phase-head">
          <div class="phase-head-left">
            <span class="phase-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <div class="phase-label">Phase 02 · Weeks 5 → 8</div>
              <h1 class="phase-title">Sessions become your <em>SOP</em>.</h1>
            </div>
          </div>
          <span class="phase-subhead">Your corpus becomes Skills →</span>
        </div>

        <div class="week-grid cols4">
          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 05</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">See your patterns.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Review your best Month 1 sessions. Where did you actually <em>get leverage</em>?</li>
              <li>Ask AI to help you <em>spot the patterns</em>.</li>
              <li>Pick your <em>top 3</em> recurring tasks — one Know, one Do, one Show.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 06</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Write one SOP.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Write your most-repeated task like you'd <em>teach a smart intern</em>.</li>
              <li>Have AI interview you to surface <em>edge cases</em> you'd forget.</li>
              <li>Add examples of <em>good and bad</em> output.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 07</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Ship one Skill.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li><em>Skill Creator</em> turns your SOP into a Skill.</li>
              <li>3–5 passes until it works on <em>3 real inputs</em>.</li>
              <li class="carry explore"><span class="ctag">Explore</span>one AI tool you've never used, on a real task</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 08</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Compose.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Build a <em>second Skill</em> in a different K/D/S category.</li>
              <li>Chain <em>two Skills</em> in one real workflow.</li>
              <li>Hand a Skill to a colleague. <em>Watch what breaks.</em></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="slide-num">12 · Phase 2</div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 18 · Phase 3 — Skills are your operating system ═══ -->
    <section class="card-deck-card deck-slide slide-phase p3" data-slide="plan-phase-3">
      <div class="phase-content stagger">
        <div class="phase-head">
          <div class="phase-head-left">
            <span class="phase-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <div class="phase-label">Phase 03 · Weeks 9 → 13</div>
              <h1 class="phase-title">Skills are your <em>operating system</em>.</h1>
            </div>
          </div>
          <span class="phase-subhead">The foundation everything runs on →</span>
        </div>

        <div class="week-grid cols5">
          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 09</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Hunt for Skills.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Browse <em>anthropic/skills</em>, skills.sh, community lists.</li>
              <li>Install <em>two Skills</em> you didn't write. Use each on a real task.</li>
              <li>Ask AI: "What Skills should I be using?" Cross-check with a second model.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 10</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Scale your library.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Add <em>two more Skills</em> in the K/D/S categories you haven't covered.</li>
              <li>AI interviews you before the SOP.</li>
              <li class="carry explore"><span class="ctag">Explore</span>NotebookLM · Nano Banana · Deep Research · Perplexity · local model</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 11</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Compose across domains.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Chain <em>3+ Skills</em> end-to-end (<em>Research → Draft → Polish</em>).</li>
              <li>Watch where handoffs break. Tighten inputs and outputs.</li>
              <li class="carry explore"><span class="ctag">Explore</span>one "must-use" from the Day 2 map you haven't tried</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 12</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">The meta move.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li>Build a <em>Skill for building Skills</em> — your taste, baked in.</li>
              <li>Run it on your existing Skills. What gets sharper?</li>
              <li class="carry explore"><span class="ctag">Explore</span>swap your default chat AI for a week</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="week-card">
            <div class="week-label">Week 13</div>
            <h4 class="week-title">Share, audit, teach.</h4>
            <ul class="week-actions">
              <li><em>Publish one Skill.</em> Install one more from someone else.</li>
              <li>Stack audit: <em>keep / drop / add</em> — Skills, tools, sources, habits.</li>
              <li>One-pager: your Skill library, one line each.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="slide-num">13 · Phase 3</div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 20 · Ramp case study ═══ -->
    <section class="card-deck-card deck-slide slide-ramp" data-slide="ramp-case">
      <div class="ramp-content stagger">
        <div class="ramp-head">
          <div>
            <div class="ramp-eyebrow">Case study · the receipts</div>
            <h1 class="ramp-title"><em>Ramp</em> — the company that went all-in.</h1>
          </div>
          <span class="ramp-context">$22B fintech · ~1,200 people · 4 quarters of accelerating revenue →</span>
        </div>

        <div class="ramp-body">
          <div class="ramp-left">
            <div class="ramp-hero">
              <span class="stat-num">99.5%</span>
              <p class="stat-label">of <em>~1,200 Ramp employees</em> are active weekly AI users. Not just engineers — finance, ops, marketing, recruiting. The whole company.</p>
            </div>
            <blockquote class="ramp-quote">
              "If you're not using Claude Code this year — <em>no matter what your role is</em> — you're probably underperforming compared to others in the company. The people still in L0 will <em>most likely not be at the company</em>."
              <cite>— Geoff Charles, CPO · April 2026</cite>
            </blockquote>
          </div>

          <div class="ramp-right">
            <div class="receipts-label">What's actually running inside</div>
            <ul class="ramp-receipts">
              <li>
                <span class="stat">~30<span class="unit">%</span></span>
                <span class="desc">of <em>merged PRs</em> written by <strong>Inspect</strong> — their internal background coding agent. Sandboxed VMs, pre-built images, runs in Slack, VS Code, Chrome, PRs, voice.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="stat">1M+</span>
                <span class="desc">lines of AI-suggested code <em>shipped in 30 days</em>. 50% weekly Claude Code adoption across engineering.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="stat">80<span class="unit">%</span></span>
                <span class="desc">reduction in <em>incident investigation time</em> — Claude Code plugged into Datadog, Sentry, logs, flags.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="stat">84<span class="unit">%</span></span>
                <span class="desc">of <em>non-engineers</em> use coding agents weekly. Finance, sales, risk, recruiting — all query Snowflake in plain English.</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="stat">350+</span>
                <span class="desc">AI workflows <em>shared peer-to-peer</em> on their internal Skills marketplace. Plus a 3-person team (Jolt AI) acquired to build the platform.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ramp-ladder">
          <span class="ladder-label">The ladder Ramp is measuring everyone on →</span>
          <div class="ladder-grid">
            <div class="ladder-rung r0">
              <span class="tier">L0</span>
              <h5>Occasional chat.</h5>
              <p>"I tried ChatGPT once." Nothing sticks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ladder-rung r1">
              <span class="tier">L1</span>
              <h5>Daily basics.</h5>
              <p>AI a few times a week. Drafts, quick answers.</p>
